name: plastic tunnel construction | plastic tunnel | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/14881/documentation

This dataset represents the production and dismantling of 1 m2 of plastic tunnel (unheated) used for agricultural production.;The plastic tunnel is made of a structure of galvanized steel, covered with a EVA (ethylene vinyl acetate) copolymer sheet. The plastic cover must be replaced every 4 years. The tunnel lifetime is typically 25 years. The greenhouse also includes a fertigation system made of a network of polyethylene pipes. Other auxiliary facilities are also considered.

This activity starts with the production of materials used to build the tunnel and permanent technical infrastructure.

This dataset includes the production of theplastic tunnel as well as the permanent technical infrastructure. For the tunnel are included its bearing structure (steel tubes) and covering materials (plastic covers). Technical infrastrctucture includes fertigation system and storage facilities.
The activity ends with the disposal of all the materials.
category: F:Construction/41:Construction of buildings/410:Construction of buildings/4100:Construction of buildings

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Time period referring to the data source: 2005-2009. Based on expert opinion data is considered to be valid at least up to 2012.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Dataset is adapted from AGRIBALYSE 1.2 database, with land occupation and transformation flows removed (these are accounted for in the crop datasets). Data was collected from French manufacturers and reported in Boulard et al. (2011).

exchanges.description: Yield = 1.0 kg/ha
